│ assert in isSingleSourceMaskImpl. We should avoid any mask classification when HasNeg is true. I will add an early break in the SK_PermuteSingleSrc case after computing HasNeg, which   │
│ prevents invoking isInsertSubvectorMask, isSelectMask, isTransposeMask, and isSpliceMask on poison masks. The function will then fall through to return Kind, preserving behavior for    │
│ valid masks and avoiding the crash.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1047i\      if (HasNeg)\n        break;' llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/BasicTTIImpl.h && submit-patch                                                                                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
