│ THOUGHT: The crash persists because improveShuffleKindFromMask still calls mask classifiers like isSelectMask on masks that contain negative (poison) elements, which triggers an        │
│ assertion in isSingleSourceMaskImpl. The localized safe fix is to early break out of the SK_PermuteSingleSrc case when HasNeg is true, right after computing HasNeg, so none of the mask │
│ classifiers are called on invalid masks. This avoids the crash without changing behavior for valid masks.                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1047a\      if (HasNeg)\n        break;' llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/BasicTTIImpl.h                                                                                                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
